Table  4  shows the proportion of texters who received help from a doctor or a therapist and the proportion who said they had not sought help anywhere other than CTL when in crisis. About a quarter (23%) of texters reported receiving help from a therapist or doctor when in a crisis and more than a quarter (28%) reported that they had no additional sources of help (including informal supports) for their current crisis other than CTL.

